# NEUEGEN Studio — environment (copy to .env; .env is gitignored)

# ── LLM provider (design agent, planner, copy) ──────────────────────────────────────────────
# Any OpenAI-compatible endpoint works. Default = DeepSeek.
DEEPSEEK_API_KEY=sk-...
# LLM_BASE_URL=https://api.deepseek.com
# LLM_MODEL=deepseek-v4-flash

# LM Studio (local model) — start the LM Studio server, then:
# LLM_BASE_URL=http://localhost:1234/v1
# LLM_MODEL=qwen2.5-7b-instruct          # whatever model id LM Studio shows
# LLM_API_KEY=                           # leave empty — no auth header is sent

# Ollama:
# LLM_BASE_URL=http://localhost:11434/v1
# LLM_MODEL=gemma2:9b

# ── TrendTrack (competitor ad ingestion — 1 credit per returned row) ────────────────────────
TRENDTRACK_API_KEY=sk_tt_...

# ── codex engine (image generation + vision extraction) ────────────────────────────────────
# CODEX_CLI=/Applications/Codex.app/Contents/Resources/codex   # override binary path
# CONCURRENCY=2          # parallel generation jobs
# COOLDOWN_MIN=30        # rate-limit cooldown minutes
# GRACE_SECONDS=10       # cancel-grace window before a job spawns

# ── Vision endpoint (optional) ────────────────────────────────────────────────
# A DEDICATED vision model, separate from the reasoning model — e.g. Gemma 3n e4b
# in LM Studio. When set, extraction / image descriptions / the agent's `look` op
# use this endpoint; DeepSeek keeps all reasoning. Codex CLI remains the fallback
# (disable it with VISION_FALLBACK=none).
# VISION_BASE_URL=http://localhost:1234/v1
# VISION_MODEL=gemma-3n-e4b
# VISION_API_KEY=
# Default VISION_MODEL is now gemma-4-e4b (run it in LM Studio). Reference extraction is
# vision-ONLY — no Codex — so a vision endpoint must be running to copy reference layers.

# ── Preferred local model (ornith9b) ──────────────────────────────────────────
# A smarter local model than Gemma. Just LOAD it in LM Studio at VISION_BASE_URL and it is used
# AUTOMATICALLY — for BOTH image analysis AND the reasoning tasks DeepSeek would do — whenever it
# is active. Detection: the SMALLEST "ornith*" model that will load is auto-preferred (so the 9b is
# chosen over a 35b that a laptop can't load), or set PREFERRED_MODEL to pin an exact id/substring.
# Not loadable → auto-fallback to Gemma (vision) / DeepSeek (reasoning), so nothing ever breaks.
# PREFERRED_MODEL=ornith-1.0-9b-mtp
